cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: QUIC Protocol Performance Evaluation Experiment
abstract: This dataset documents an experiment designed to evaluate the performance
  characteristics of various QUIC protocol implementations under different bandwidth
  constraints. The methodology involved establishing a controlled environment on two
  nodes (tartu and tallinn) through automated bootstrapping, system configuration,
  and package installation steps. Multiple configurations were tested, including varying
  bandwidth limits and transport layer implementations. Data collection focused on
  measuring goodput performance, execution time, and success rates via client and
  server processes, generating JSON reports and visualization plots for analysis.
  Per-run logs and evaluation outputs are archived to facilitate detailed investigation
  of the experiment’s results.
